com.phonegap.calendar.android.model
Class Where

java.lang.Object
  com.phonegap.calendar.android.model.Where

public class Where
extends java.lang.Object

A place (such as an event location) associated with the containing entity. The type of the association is determined by the rel attribute; the details of the location are contained in an embedded or linked-to Contact entry. A Where element is more general than a GeoPt element. The former identifies a place using a text description and/or a Contact entry, while the latter identifies a place using a specific geographic location.

Since:
2.2
Author:
Nicolas Garnier, Sergio Martinez Rodriguez

rel

public java.lang.String rel
Specifies the relationship between the containing entity and the contained location. Possible values (see below) are defined by other elements. For example, When defines REL_EVENT. Valid values are REL_EVENT, REL_EVENT_ALTERNATE and REL_EVENT_PARKING.
